Watch how my facial hair has evolved over the years and how I use @braun_global’s new Series 7 both as a tool of self-expression and to manage my desired look on a daily basis! Well-groomed stubble or clean-shaven, whatever look you desire the Series 7 is here to help you #SayItWithAShave

Follow this link (https://bit.ly/3k22n28) to learn more about the Series 7 and comment below with the funniest moment of your shaving journey! Ad

#BraunUK #SayItWithAShave

node.text:
Barn Door Back Workout 🛡

All the training volume is right here in this workout 😂 I definitely needed a rest day after this one.

The workout:
1. Deadlifts 5x10/10/8/6/4 into ⬇️ (excuse the face)
2. Pull ups 5xfailure
3. One arm rows 3x10 + dropset
4. Machine pull overs 4x12
5. Machine pull down 4x10
6. T bar rows 4x15/12/10/8 + dropset
7. Machine rear delt fly 4x15-20

Training vest from @rise - code: MARINO

Pulling 5 plates for the first time in a while which felt good! Will aim to make this a comfortable working weight over the next few months 👌🏼

node.text:
Workout Rule Number 1 - never forget the post workout selfie, otherwise the workout didn’t count.

Joggers from @RISE use C0DE: MARINO for a discount on the whole site 👊🏼

Chest and a little bit of delts 💪🏼

Great session down @thirdspacelondon city, working my way up on bench press! Let’s see if we can get that weight for 10 soon!

The workout:
1. Flat bench 3x6 drop set to 100 for max reps
2. Incline DB press 4x8-10 superset ⬇️
3. Incline DB fly 4x12
4. Chain dips 4x15
5. Lateral raises 5x15 superset ⬇️
6. Pause raises 5xfailure

Finished the workout with a bit of core! In London for @domiwaffles x Bo&Tee launch so of course will be training in all the great gyms up here!

Joggers from @rise

node.text: Most people don’t know this, but your knees are actually quite thirsty and you should give them a little drink of water whenever you can

Raw Leg day 🤘🏼

Great hammie focused leg session down @kfitnessstudio 💪🏼 first time doing heavyish deadlifts for a while and it felt good!

1. Walking lunges into back squats 3x8-10 each
2. Heavy deads 4x6-8 (190kg in clip)
3. Nordic curl 3x8
4. Goblet squats 3x12 + drop set
5. Hamstring curls 3x10
6. Single leg deads 3x12 each leg

We threw in some calves in there as well 😂  I’m usually training legs once per week. One week quad focused, and the other week hamstring focused as I find this works best for me.
